[Grafton,

June, 1881.] Kinsley v. Norris & a.

Subject to the plaintiff’s exception, the court granted certain motions made by the defendants, and denied certain other motions *640made by tbe plaintiff. The exceptions were overruled on the ground that they raised no question of law.

C. It. Morrison and F. D. Currier, for the plaintiff. Carpenter Carpenter, Burleigh Adams, Bingham, Mitchell $ Batchellor, and Bingham Aldrich, for the defendants. Allen, J., did not sit: the others concurred.
